-- Greek Bond Trading on HDAT Jumped 120% to 1.8 Billion Euros in September
-- B y   M a t t h e w   B r o w n
-- 2010-10-13T08:43:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-13/greek-bond-trading-on-hdat-jumped-120-to-1-8-billion-euros-in-september.html
Greek bond trading on the electronic
secondary securities market, known as HDAT, climbed 120 percent
to 1.8 billion euros ($2.5 billion) in September, according to
the Bank of Greece.  The most-actively traded security was the three-year note
due in March 2011 with 451 million euros of transactions, the
central bank said in an e-mail. Of the 1,400 orders executed on
HDAT, 57 percent were sell orders and 43 percent buy orders, the
bank said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
